{% extends "layouts/doc-layout" %}

{% block title %}Default Filter - Wisp Template Documentation{% end %}

{% block body %}
<h1>Default Filter</h1>

<p>Returns a fallback value when the input is <code>nil</code> or an empty string. Non-empty values (including <code>false</code> and <code>0</code>) are passed through unchanged.</p>

<h2>Syntax</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% .value | default "fallback" %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>

<h2>Examples</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% nil | default "N/A" %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> N/A</p>
<p>A <code>nil</code> value triggers the default.</p>

<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% "" | default "anonymous" %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> anonymous</p>
<p>An empty string also triggers the default.</p>

<pre><code>{% raw %}
{% .count | default 0 %}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> (the value of <code>.count</code>, or <code>0</code> if it is nil/empty)</p>
<p>The default value can be any type — a number, string, or boolean.</p>

<h2>Notes</h2>
<ul>
  <li><code>default</code> triggers on <code>nil</code> and empty string (<code>""</code>) only.</li>
  <li><code>false</code> and <code>0</code> are <strong>not</strong> considered empty — they pass through unchanged.</li>
  <li>Use <code>default</code> to guard against missing template variables rather than writing <code>{% raw %}{% if %}{% endraw %}</code> blocks.</li>
</ul>
{% end %}
